  "target_response": {
    "text": "Your routine sounds fundamentally healthy, so keep it mostly as is. One bathroom wake-up a night with a quick return to sleep is very common, and a briefly quick heartbeat after walking to the bathroom and back is a normal response to getting up, settling once you're still — a racing or irregular heartbeat that starts at rest or keeps you awake would be the different, see-a-doctor kind. You logged about 7.2 hours, which is a good total. Two small levers fit your pattern: taper fluids in the last stretch of the evening so the wake-up is less likely, and keep the trip back to bed dim and screen-free so the arousal stays shallow. Since your sleep is manually logged, noting the rough wake time too would sharpen what I can tell you.",
